headline: Down Over 10%, This Elite High-Yield Dividend Stock Is a Great buy for Passive Income Right Now
summary: Federal Realty has increased its dividend for 57 straight years.  Shares of Federal Realty Investment Trust (NYSE: FRT) have slumped more than 10% over the past year.  One silver lining of its sell-off is that its dividend yield has risen and is now over 4.5%.
